<div class="content"><div class="main large"><h3>Dropdowns</h3>
  The <i>caret</i> mixin creates a caret that can be placed inline with text.<br>
  The <i>dropdown-menu</i> mixin wraps around the menu options in the dropdown.<br>
  The class <i>divider</i> can be used to make a line separator in the drop down menu.<br>
  The attribute <i>disabled="disabled"</i> can be used to disable menu options.
  <br><br>

<code><pre>
.caret {
  @include caret(white);
}
.dropdown-menu {
  @include dropdown-menu(false);
}

...

&lt;div class="dropdown"&gt;

  &lt;a class="btn dropdown-toggle" id="dropdownMenu" toggle-type="dropdown"&gt;
    Dropdown Button&lt;span class="caret"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;/a&gt;

  &lt;ul class="dropdown-menu" role="menu" aria-labelledby="dropdownMenu"&gt;
    &lt;li class="header"&gt;Dropdown Header&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a role="menuitem" href="#"&gt;Action&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a role="menuitem" href="#"&gt;Another action&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a role="menuitem" href="#"&gt;Something&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li class="divider"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a role="menuitem" href="#"&gt;Separated link&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li class="divider"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;&lt;a disabled="disabled" role="menuitem" href="#"&gt;Disabled&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;
</pre></code>

</div></div>
<div class="sidebar"><b>Mixin Definition</b>
  <br><br>

  @mixin dropdown-menu($back-color: $default-dropdown-background, $text-color: $default-dropdown-text-color, $use-caret: true)
  <br><br>

  Optional Parameters:
  <br>
  <ol>
    <li>background color (default is $default-dropdown-background)</li>
    <li>text color (default is $default-text-color)</li>
    <li>use caret (default is $use-caret)</li>
  </ol>
</div>

<div class="content large"><div class="main large">
  Use <i>dropdown</i> as the class to wrap around the element being used to launch the dropdown, and the dropdown menu itself. The element used to trigger the dropdown should have class <i>dropdown-toggle</i> and attribute <i>toggle-type="dropdown"</i>. Use <i>dropdown-menu</i> as the class name for the dropdown menu.
  <br><br>

  When using the <i>dropdown-menu</i> mixin, the first color provided will supply the background-color. The second color is for the text. All parameters are optional. If only the caret state and a colour are provided, the color will be used on the background, and the text colour will be set to default.<br>
  The default background color is #ECECF2, the default text color is #6D707B, the default to use a caret or not is false.
  <br><br>

